      "text": "Marineland began as Marine Studios in 1938, the first oceanarium and a hotspot for Hollywood underwater shoots.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1,
        9,
        18
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marineland%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "After the aquarium opened, local businessmen built a small town around the studio, shaping Marineland’s early growth.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://marineland.omeka.net/exhibits/show/marineland-as-florida-tourism/tourist-paradise"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Marineland is its own municipality with a governing body, distinct from the surrounding counties.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        15
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marineland%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The town officially incorporated in 1940, just two years after the studio opened.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        19
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marineland%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Summers in Marineland are hot and humid, while winters stay mild, typical of Florida’s coastal climate.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        21
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marineland%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
